result.name: Luna Cake

reviews.text: Their cheesecake was authentic and definitely tasted like it's from Hokkaido. Amazing richness and excellent presentation cements this as a must try if you are in the vicinity. We had the cheesecake, crunbar (their crunchy cheese filled eclair) and a houjicha latte. All were out of this world.

A great place for a cup of coffee and a cake!
Hidden away from the mall, it's a great place to relax.

Both the coffee and cakes are amazing!
Must try the Rose Lychee Cheesecake

Really nice cheeses cakes, 
Value for money.

One of the best cheese cakes I ever hv,  well balanced btwn texture n cheesie favors.  A happy surprise with the crunbar for its crispy warm wrapping n cold cream cheese core.  I love their coffee which is well blended btwn smoothness n bean taste.  The mock champagne is refreshing with a hint of citrus zeal.  Good food quality at reasonable prices with frdly n helpful services.  Unfortunately the wagyu beef pies r sold out during my visit n will definitely come back again for more.

Interesting way of doing cheesecake. Its has 2 layers. 1 is creamy mousse like and the bottom one is cheesy texture. Not very sweet so it is nice when you do not really have a sweet tooth.   Original cheesecake is HKD38

reviews.text: Smaller mall in Tsim Sha Tsui, specialising more on smaller boutique stores. The mall also has a nice, artsy outdoor area on the ground floor. Overall you probably won't be staying here for very long, but the visit can be pleasant. There will likely be a lot more to do around here as the bigger extension to K11 opens later this year.
The mall is undergoing renovation but you can still find lots of good restaurants and shops there. It is convenient where you can connect to MTR station.
Very good location with many shops. Always visit here. Some restaurant is great. Love Empire duck./ ice cream shop.

Great mall if you want to see something different! Always has different art exhibits going on. Also has a lot of designer and boutique stores along with the usual ones at a variety of price ranges. Love it!
Very clean and new shopping mall, connected to a hotel and very close to MTR station. Good dining choices offered (not chained restaurants), there is a grocery store too.

result.name: Luna Cafe

reviews.text: 叫左一客tea set, 無期待下幾有驚喜。歌客甜點最啱心水嘅地方就係唔太租 （人就是矛盾😆）， 杯啡見到有誠意，諗起Ritz Carlton $100杯連花都無拉, 純粹一堆泡係面，真心唔掂。明嘅，果日我係飲左杯「租」。

北海道的Luna Cake芝士蛋糕專門店聽說有點名氣💨😊😎 就和三五成群一班愛食甜品的朋友來試試看~ CRUNBAR芝士忌廉脆條 滿布杏仁粒的外皮酥脆,雪糕MIX幼滑芝士忌廉，輕輕咬開吃下會有滿滿的飽滿感,但不會太膩滯 芝士蛋糕LUNA都是由富良野出產,質量有保證,每天由日本工場限量製作，再空運到港，新鮮之餘更是無添加，絕不含增味劑、人造糖或防腐劑等 有玫瑰乾花的玫瑰荔枝芝士蛋糕,蛋糕混入了荔枝果肉， 檸檬芝士蛋糕小清新感而不膩,十分開胃 這家店內有設20多個座位可以坐，如果和朋友行到累來吃芝士蛋糕和聊天也不錯喔 看到其他款式其實都吸引，找天要再來試呢~~~
點了一個雞扒意粉及鮮橙汁，價格稍高，但味道好且服務好
